│ 14095 /// Merges shuffle masks and emits final shuffle instruction, if required. It                              │
│ 14096 /// supports shuffling of 2 input vectors. It implements lazy shuffles emission,                           │
│ 14097 /// when the actual shuffle instruction is generated only if this is actually                              │
│ 14098 /// required. Otherwise, the shuffle instruction emission is delayed till the                              │
│ 14099 /// end of the process, to reduce the number of emitted instructions and further                           │
│ 14100 /// analysis/transformations.                                                                              │
│ 14101 /// The class also will look through the previously emitted shuffle instructions                           │
│ 14102 /// and properly mark indices in mask as undef.                                                            │
│ 14103 /// For example, given the code                                                                            │
│ 14104 /// \code                                                                                                  │
│ 14105 /// %s1 = shufflevector <2 x ty> %0, poison, <1, 0>                                                        │
│ 14106 /// %s2 = shufflevector <2 x ty> %1, poison, <1, 0>                                                        │
│ 14107 /// \endcode                                                                                               │
│ 14108 /// and if need to emit shuffle of %s1 and %s2 with mask <1, 0, 3, 2>, it will                             │
│ 14109 /// look through %s1 and %s2 and emit                                                                      │
│ 14110 /// \code                                                                                                  │
│ 14111 /// %res = shufflevector <2 x ty> %0, %1, <0, 1, 2, 3>                                                     │
│ 14112 /// \endcode                                                                                               │
│ 14113 /// instead.                                                                                               │
│ 14114 /// If 2 operands are of different size, the smallest one will be resized and                              │
│ 14115 /// the mask recalculated properly.                                                                        │
│ 14116 /// For example, given the code                                                                            │
│ 14117 /// \code                                                                                                  │
